.TH RECIPE-HELPERS 7 "2026-03-12" "recipe 0.1.3" "Recipe Helpers"
.SH NAME
recipe-helpers \- current helper surface exposed to Rhai recipes
.SH OVERVIEW
This page documents the helper names currently registered by
\fBtools/recipe/src/helpers/mod.rs\fR. It is intended as a stable LLM-oriented
catalog: each helper entry uses the same schema and describes current behavior
rather than future spec intent.
.PP
Schema used below:
.IP "\[bu]" 4
\fBSignature\fR: Rhai call shape
.IP "\[bu]" 4
\fBReturns\fR: result value
.IP "\[bu]" 4
\fBFails when\fR: common failure modes
.IP "\[bu]" 4
\fBExample\fR: minimal concrete invocation
.SH PATH HELPERS
.TP
\fBjoin_path\fR
Signature: \fBjoin_path(a, b)\fR
.br
Returns: joined path string
.br
Fails when: never for ordinary string inputs
.br
Example: \fBjoin_path(BUILD_DIR, "src")\fR
.TP
\fBbasename\fR
Signature: \fBbasename(path)\fR
.br
Returns: final path component as string
.br
Fails when: never for ordinary string inputs
.br
Example: \fBbasename("/tmp/foo.tar.xz")\fR
.TP
\fBdirname\fR
Signature: \fBdirname(path)\fR
.br
Returns: parent path as string
.br
Fails when: never for ordinary string inputs
.br
Example: \fBdirname("/tmp/foo.tar.xz")\fR
.SH STRING HELPERS
.TP
\fBtrim\fR
Signature: \fBtrim(s)\fR
.br
Returns: trimmed string
.br
Fails when: never
.br
Example: \fBtrim("  hello  ")\fR
.TP
\fBstarts_with\fR
Signature: \fBstarts_with(s, prefix)\fR
.br
Returns: boolean
.br
Fails when: never
.br
Example: \fBstarts_with(url, "https://")\fR
.TP
\fBends_with\fR
Signature: \fBends_with(s, suffix)\fR
.br
Returns: boolean
.br
Fails when: never
.br
Example: \fBends_with(archive, ".tar.xz")\fR
.TP
\fBcontains\fR
Signature: \fBcontains(s, pat)\fR
.br
Returns: boolean
.br
Fails when: never
.br
Example: \fBcontains(text, "Release")\fR
.TP
\fBreplace\fR
Signature: \fBreplace(s, from, to)\fR
.br
Returns: replaced string
.br
Fails when: never
.br
Example: \fBreplace(version, "v", "")\fR
.TP
\fBsplit\fR
Signature: \fBsplit(s, sep)\fR
.br
Returns: array of strings
.br
Fails when: never
.br
Example: \fBsplit("a:b:c", ":")\fR
.SH LOGGING HELPERS
.TP
\fBlog\fR
Signature: \fBlog(msg)\fR
.br
Returns: \fB()\fR
.br
Fails when: stderr formatting fails
.br
Example: \fBlog("building kernel")\fR
.TP
\fBdebug\fR
Signature: \fBdebug(msg)\fR
.br
Returns: \fB()\fR
.br
Fails when: stderr formatting fails
.br
Example: \fBdebug("checking build cache")\fR
.TP
\fBwarn\fR
Signature: \fBwarn(msg)\fR
.br
Returns: \fB()\fR
.br
Fails when: stderr formatting fails
.br
Example: \fBwarn("falling back to plain copy")\fR
.SH SHELL HELPERS
.TP
\fBshell\fR
Signature: \fBshell(cmd)\fR
.br
Returns: \fB()\fR
.br
Fails when: \fBsh -c\fR execution fails or exits non-zero
.br
Example: \fBshell("make -j$(nproc)")\fR
.TP
\fBshell_in\fR
Signature: \fBshell_in(dir, cmd)\fR
.br
Returns: \fB()\fR
.br
Fails when: directory change or shell command fails
.br
Example: \fBshell_in(ctx.src_dir, "./configure")\fR
.TP
\fBshell_status\fR
Signature: \fBshell_status(cmd)\fR
.br
Returns: integer exit code
.br
Fails when: the shell process cannot be started
.br
Example: \fBshell_status("test -f /usr/bin/bash")\fR
.TP
\fBshell_status_in\fR
Signature: \fBshell_status_in(dir, cmd)\fR
.br
Returns: integer exit code
.br
Fails when: directory change or shell startup fails
.br
Example: \fBshell_status_in(ctx.src_dir, "make test")\fR
.TP
\fBshell_output\fR
Signature: \fBshell_output(cmd)\fR
.br
Returns: stdout string
.br
Fails when: shell command fails
.br
Example: \fBtrim(shell_output("uname -m"))\fR
.TP
\fBshell_output_in\fR
Signature: \fBshell_output_in(dir, cmd)\fR
.br
Returns: stdout string
.br
Fails when: directory change or shell command fails
.br
Example: \fBshell_output_in(ctx.src_dir, "git rev-parse HEAD")\fR
.SH FILE AND TEXT HELPERS
.TP
\fBread_file\fR
Signature: \fBread_file(path)\fR
.br
Returns: file contents as string
.br
Fails when: file does not exist or cannot be read
.br
Example: \fBread_file("/etc/os-release")\fR
.TP
\fBread_file_or_empty\fR
Signature: \fBread_file_or_empty(path)\fR
.br
Returns: file contents or empty string
.br
Fails when: never for missing files
.br
Example: \fBread_file_or_empty("/etc/hostname")\fR
.TP
\fBwrite_file\fR
Signature: \fBwrite_file(path, content)\fR
.br
Returns: \fB()\fR
.br
Fails when: parent path is unwritable or file creation fails
.br
Example: \fBwrite_file(join_path(BUILD_DIR, "config"), "x=1\\n")\fR
.TP
\fBappend_file\fR
Signature: \fBappend_file(path, content)\fR
.br
Returns: \fB()\fR
.br
Fails when: file open or append fails
.br
Example: \fBappend_file("/etc/profile", "export FOO=1\\n")\fR
.TP
\fBappend_line_if_missing\fR
Signature: \fBappend_line_if_missing(path, line)\fR
.br
Returns: boolean indicating whether a line was appended
.br
Fails when: file read or append fails
.br
Example: \fBappend_line_if_missing(passwd, "builder:x:1000:1000::/home/builder:/bin/bash")\fR
.TP
\fBreplace_in_file\fR
Signature: \fBreplace_in_file(path, from, to)\fR
.br
Returns: \fB()\fR
.br
Fails when: file read or write fails
.br
Example: \fBreplace_in_file(desktop, "Exec=kitty", "Exec=/usr/bin/kitty")\fR
.TP
\fBglob_list\fR
Signature: \fBglob_list(pattern)\fR
.br
Returns: array of matching string paths
.br
Fails when: the glob pattern is invalid
.br
Example: \fBglob_list(join_path(font_dir, "*.ttf"))\fR
.TP
\fBglob_exists\fR
Signature: \fBglob_exists(pattern)\fR
.br
Returns: boolean
.br
Fails when: the glob pattern is invalid
.br
Example: \fBglob_exists(join_path(font_dir, "*.otf"))\fR
.SH FILESYSTEM HELPERS
.TP
\fBexists\fR
Signature: \fBexists(path)\fR
.br
Returns: boolean, including dangling symlinks
.br
Fails when: never
.br
Example: \fBexists("/tmp/link")\fR
.TP
\fBfile_exists\fR, \fBis_file\fR
Signature: \fBfile_exists(path)\fR
.br
Returns: boolean
.br
Fails when: never
.br
Example: \fBis_file(ctx.archive)\fR
.TP
\fBdir_exists\fR, \fBis_dir\fR
Signature: \fBdir_exists(path)\fR
.br
Returns: boolean
.br
Fails when: never
.br
Example: \fBis_dir(ctx.src_dir)\fR
.TP
\fBmkdir\fR
Signature: \fBmkdir(path)\fR
.br
Returns: \fB()\fR
.br
Fails when: directory creation fails
.br
Example: \fBmkdir(join_path(env("HOME"), ".local/bin"))\fR
.TP
\fBrm\fR
Signature: \fBrm(pattern)\fR
.br
Returns: \fB()\fR
.br
Fails when: glob expansion or removal fails
.br
Example: \fBrm(join_path(BUILD_DIR, "*"))\fR
.TP
\fBmv\fR
Signature: \fBmv(src, dst)\fR
.br
Returns: \fB()\fR
.br
Fails when: rename fails
.br
Example: \fBmv(ctx.downloaded, dst)\fR
.TP
\fBln\fR
Signature: \fBln(target, link)\fR
.br
Returns: \fB()\fR
.br
Fails when: symlinks are unsupported or link creation fails
.br
Example: \fBln("/usr/bin/python3", "/usr/bin/python")\fR
.TP
\fBln_force\fR
Signature: \fBln_force(target, link)\fR
.br
Returns: \fB()\fR
.br
Fails when: destination is a directory, symlinks are unsupported, or replacement fails
.br
Example: \fBln_force("/usr/bin/kitty", join_path(bin_dir, "xterm"))\fR
.TP
\fBchmod\fR
Signature: \fBchmod(path, mode)\fR
.br
Returns: \fB()\fR
.br
Fails when: chmod fails on Unix
.br
Example: \fBchmod(dst, 0o755)\fR
.TP
\fBcopy_into_dir\fR
Signature: \fBcopy_into_dir(pattern, dest_dir)\fR
.br
Returns: \fB()\fR
.br
Fails when: destination is not a directory, pattern is invalid, or no files match
.br
Example: \fBcopy_into_dir(join_path(src_dir, "*.ttf"), fonts_dir)\fR
.TP
\fBcopy_file\fR
Signature: \fBcopy_file(src, dst)\fR
.br
Returns: \fB()\fR
.br
Fails when: source is not a file or copy fails
.br
Example: \fBcopy_file(ctx.kernel_image, join_path(boot_dir, "vmlinuz"))\fR
.TP
\fBcopy_file_reflink\fR
Signature: \fBcopy_file_reflink(src, dst)\fR
.br
Returns: \fB()\fR
.br
Fails when: source is not a file or fallback copy fails
.br
Example: \fBcopy_file_reflink(preseed, join_path(staging_dir, "ks.cfg"))\fR
.TP
\fBcopy_tree_contents\fR
Signature: \fBcopy_tree_contents(src_dir, dst_dir)\fR
.br
Returns: \fB()\fR
.br
Fails when: source or destination is not a directory, or recursive copy fails
.br
Example: \fBcopy_tree_contents(rootfs_seed, slot_root)\fR
.TP
\fBcopy_first_existing\fR
Signature: \fBcopy_first_existing(sources, dst)\fR
.br
Returns: string path of the source that was copied
.br
Fails when: no listed source exists as a file or the copy fails
.br
Example: \fBcopy_first_existing([a, b], join_path(bin_dir, "mkisofs"))\fR
.SH ACQUIRE HELPERS
.TP
\fBdownload\fR
Signature: \fBdownload(url, dest)\fR
.br
Returns: destination path string
.br
Fails when: download fails or destination cannot be written
.br
Example: \fBdownload(ctx.url, join_path(BUILD_DIR, "src.tar.xz"))\fR
.TP
\fBverify_sha256\fR
Signature: \fBverify_sha256(path, expected)\fR
.br
Returns: \fB()\fR
.br
Fails when: hash mismatch or file read fails
.br
Example: \fBverify_sha256(archive, ctx.sha256)\fR
.TP
\fBfetch_sha256\fR
Signature: \fBfetch_sha256(url, filename)\fR
.br
Returns: matching checksum string
.br
Fails when: checksum file cannot be fetched or parsed
.br
Example: \fBfetch_sha256(checksums_url, "foo.tar.xz")\fR
.TP
\fBverify_sha512\fR
Signature: \fBverify_sha512(path, expected)\fR
.br
Returns: \fB()\fR
.br
Fails when: hash mismatch or file read fails
.br
Example: \fBverify_sha512(archive, ctx.sha512)\fR
.TP
\fBverify_blake3\fR
Signature: \fBverify_blake3(path, expected)\fR
.br
Returns: \fB()\fR
.br
Fails when: hash mismatch or file read fails
.br
Example: \fBverify_blake3(archive, ctx.blake3)\fR
.TP
\fBhttp_get\fR
Signature: \fBhttp_get(url)\fR
.br
Returns: response body string
.br
Fails when: request fails
.br
Example: \fBhttp_get(releases_url)\fR
.TP
\fBgithub_latest_release\fR
Signature: \fBgithub_latest_release(repo)\fR
.br
Returns: latest release version string with common prefixes stripped
.br
Fails when: GitHub request fails or response shape is invalid
.br
Example: \fBgithub_latest_release("sharkdp/bat")\fR
.TP
\fBgithub_latest_tag\fR
Signature: \fBgithub_latest_tag(repo)\fR
.br
Returns: latest tag string with common prefixes stripped
.br
Fails when: GitHub request fails or response shape is invalid
.br
Example: \fBgithub_latest_tag("BurntSushi/ripgrep")\fR
.TP
\fBparse_version\fR
Signature: \fBparse_version(s)\fR
.br
Returns: normalized version string
.br
Fails when: never
.br
Example: \fBparse_version("release-1.2.3")\fR
.TP
\fBgithub_download_release\fR
Signature: \fBgithub_download_release(repo, pattern, dest_dir)\fR
.br
Returns: downloaded asset path
.br
Fails when: release discovery or download fails
.br
Example: \fBgithub_download_release("owner/proj", "x86_64.rpm", BUILD_DIR)\fR
.TP
\fBextract_from_tarball\fR
Signature: \fBextract_from_tarball(url, pattern, dest)\fR
.br
Returns: extracted path
.br
Fails when: download, tar extraction, or match selection fails
.br
Example: \fBextract_from_tarball(url, "bin/tool", BUILD_DIR)\fR
.TP
\fBgit_clone\fR
Signature: \fBgit_clone(url, dest_dir)\fR
.br
Returns: clone path
.br
Fails when: git invocation fails
.br
Example: \fBgit_clone(ctx.repo, BUILD_DIR)\fR
.TP
\fBgit_clone_depth\fR
Signature: \fBgit_clone_depth(url, dest_dir, depth)\fR
.br
Returns: clone path
.br
Fails when: git invocation fails
.br
Example: \fBgit_clone_depth(ctx.repo, BUILD_DIR, 1)\fR
.TP
\fBtorrent\fR
Signature: \fBtorrent(url, dest_dir)\fR
.br
Returns: downloaded path
.br
Fails when: torrent download fails
.br
Example: \fBtorrent(ctx.magnet, BUILD_DIR)\fR
.TP
\fBdownload_with_resume\fR
Signature: \fBdownload_with_resume(url, dest)\fR
.br
Returns: destination path
.br
Fails when: HTTP range download fails
.br
Example: \fBdownload_with_resume(ctx.url, join_path(BUILD_DIR, "iso"))\fR
.SH BUILD HELPERS
.TP
\fBextract\fR
Signature: \fBextract(archive, dest)\fR
.br
Returns: \fB()\fR
.br
Fails when: archive type is unsupported or extraction fails
.br
Example: \fBextract(archive, BUILD_DIR)\fR
.TP
\fBextract_with_format\fR
Signature: \fBextract_with_format(archive, dest, format)\fR
.br
Returns: \fB()\fR
.br
Fails when: format is unsupported or extraction fails
.br
Example: \fBextract_with_format(archive, BUILD_DIR, "tar.xz")\fR
.SH PROCESS AND PACKAGE HELPERS
.TP
\fBenv\fR
Signature: \fBenv(name)\fR
.br
Returns: environment variable value or empty string
.br
Fails when: never
.br
Example: \fBenv("HOME")\fR
.TP
\fBset_env\fR
Signature: \fBset_env(name, value)\fR
.br
Returns: \fB()\fR
.br
Fails when: environment mutation fails
.br
Example: \fBset_env("PATH", new_path)\fR
.TP
\fBcheck_disk_space\fR
Signature: \fBcheck_disk_space(path, required_bytes)\fR
.br
Returns: \fB()\fR
.br
Fails when: available space is below requirement or \fBdf\fR invocation fails
.br
Example: \fBcheck_disk_space(BUILD_DIR, 20 * 1024 * 1024 * 1024)\fR
.TP
\fBexec\fR
Signature: \fBexec(cmd, args)\fR
.br
Returns: integer exit code
.br
Fails when: process startup fails
.br
Example: \fBexec("make", ["-j8"])\fR
.TP
\fBexec_output\fR
Signature: \fBexec_output(cmd, args)\fR
.br
Returns: stdout string
.br
Fails when: process startup fails or exits non-zero
.br
Example: \fBtrim(exec_output("pkg-config", ["--modversion", "glib-2.0"]))\fR
.TP
\fBrpm_installed\fR
Signature: \fBrpm_installed(name)\fR
.br
Returns: boolean
.br
Fails when: never; returns false if \fBrpm\fR cannot be queried
.br
Example: \fBrpm_installed("git")\fR
.TP
\fBrpm_version\fR
Signature: \fBrpm_version(name)\fR
.br
Returns: installed version string
.br
Fails when: package is absent or rpm query fails
.br
Example: \fBrpm_version("bash")\fR
.TP
\fBdnf_package_available\fR
Signature: \fBdnf_package_available(name)\fR
.br
Returns: boolean
.br
Fails when: never; returns false if \fBdnf\fR query fails
.br
Example: \fBdnf_package_available("ripgrep")\fR
.TP
\fBdnf_install\fR
Signature: \fBdnf_install(packages)\fR
.br
Returns: \fB()\fR
.br
Fails when: package list is empty or \fBsudo -n dnf install -y\fR fails
.br
Example: \fBdnf_install(["gcc", "make"])\fR
.TP
\fBdnf_install_allow_erasing\fR
Signature: \fBdnf_install_allow_erasing(packages)\fR
.br
Returns: \fB()\fR
.br
Fails when: package list is empty or DNF invocation fails
.br
Example: \fBdnf_install_allow_erasing(["mesa-libGL"])\fR
.TP
\fBdnf_add_repo\fR
Signature: \fBdnf_add_repo(url)\fR
.br
Returns: \fB()\fR
.br
Fails when: \fBsudo -n dnf config-manager --add-repo\fR fails
.br
Example: \fBdnf_add_repo("https://download.example.invalid/repo.repo")\fR
.TP
\fBdnf_download\fR
Signature: \fBdnf_download(packages, dest_dir, arches[, resolve])\fR
.br
Returns: array of downloaded RPM file paths created by the invocation
.br
Fails when: package list or arch list is empty, destination setup fails, or DNF download fails
.br
Example: \fBdnf_download(["kernel-devel"], BUILD_DIR, ["x86_64"], true)\fR
.SH LLM HELPERS
.TP
\fBllm_extract\fR
Signature: \fBllm_extract(content, prompt)\fR
.br
Returns: string
.br
Fails when: backend is unavailable
.br
Example: \fBllm_extract(html, "extract the latest stable version")\fR
.TP
\fBllm_find_latest_version\fR
Signature: \fBllm_find_latest_version(url, project)\fR
.br
Returns: string
.br
Fails when: backend is unavailable
.br
Example: \fBllm_find_latest_version(releases_url, "ripgrep")\fR
.TP
\fBllm_find_download_url\fR
Signature: \fBllm_find_download_url(content, criteria)\fR
.br
Returns: string
.br
Fails when: backend is unavailable
.br
Example: \fBllm_find_download_url(html, "linux x86_64 tar.xz")\fR
.SH SOURCE OF TRUTH
The canonical helper registration path is
\fBtools/recipe/src/helpers/mod.rs\fR. If this page and the code disagree, trust
the code and refresh the helper catalog.
.SH SEE ALSO
\fBrecipe\fR(1),
